fragment_downloaded_cb({"url": "gtklabel.html#gtk_label_get_layout_offsets", "fragment": "Gtk.Label.get_layout_offsets \ngtk_label_get_layout_offsets \nGtk.prototype.get_layout_offsets \nObtains the coordinates where the label will draw the Pango.Layout representing the text in the label useful to convert mouse events into coordinates inside the Pango.Layout e.g. to take some action if some part of the label is clicked. Remember when using the Pango.Layout functions you need to convert to and from pixels using PANGO_PIXELS not introspectable or Pango.SCALE. \nParameters \na Gtk.Label \nObtains the coordinates where the label will draw the PangoLayout representing the text in the label useful to convert mouse events into coordinates inside the PangoLayout e.g. to take some action if some part of the label is clicked. Remember when using the PangoLayout functions you need to convert to and from pixels using PANGO_PIXELS or PANGO_SCALE. \nParameters \na GtkLabel \nlocation to store X offset of layout or NULL \nlocation to store Y offset of layout or NULL \nObtains the coordinates where the label will draw the Pango.Layout representing the text in the label useful to convert mouse events into coordinates inside the Pango.Layout e.g. to take some action if some part of the label is clicked. Remember when using the Pango.Layout functions you need to convert to and from pixels using PANGO_PIXELS not introspectable or Pango.SCALE. \nParameters \na Gtk.Label \n"});